{
    "title": "Allowed or Not",
    "level": "B1",
    "pattern": {
        "title": "Permission: saa, ei saa, ei tarvii",
        "summary": "'Saa' covers permission: saaks tääl polttaa? = is smoking allowed here?, ei saa = not allowed. The opposite of must is 'ei tarvii' (don't have to) - a different thing than 'ei saa', and mixing them up changes the meaning completely.",
        "examples": [
            "Saaks tääl polttaa? = Is smoking allowed here?",
            "Sun ei tarvii tulla, jos et jaksa. = You don't have to come if you're not up to it.",
            "Koiran saa ottaa mukaan. = You're allowed to bring a dog."
        ]
    },
